__comment: • Visit the README.md file for more information on how this filter works.
• Properties starting with underscores are comments and not used in the script.
• CTRL + F a filter or modAction to find what you're looking for.
• Use Visual Studio Code to update this JSON more comfortably.
• Basic: profanity filter that is applied to all incoming player messages.
• Extended: profanity filter that is applied to all incoming reports from players.
__collection: • A collection of key-value pairs used for string builders anywhere in this JSON.
• Each key is case sensitive and must represent a string array value.
• Adding a key in any nested string array in `stringBuilder.builder` supplements
that array with the values of that key.
• Warning: use unique, eccentric key names to prevent accidental supplimenting.
__stringBuilders: • Separator: a character that separates each builder section.
• builder: multiple arrays (sections) that are appended to one another.

__message: • The profanity in basic `message` is applied to all incoming player messages.
• Notify: log the message without taking any moderation action.
__name: • The profanity in basic `name` is applied to all incoming player names.
• Notify: log the name without taking any moderation action.
__hardName: • The profanity in basic `hardName` is applied to all incoming player names.
• This profanity filter reads through the player name.
• Notify: log the name without taking any moderation action.
